title: High school football: Nazareth cruises against St. Viator
text:
High school football: Nazareth cruises against St. Viator   12:34 a.m. CDT By SUBURBAN LIFE MEDIA 
ARLINGTON HEIGHTS â€“ Nazareth built a 21-7 lead and cruised to a 49-22 win against St. Viator on Oct. 23. 
The Roadrunners finished the regular season with a 6-2 record (5-2 East Suburban Catholic Conference) and are in line to host a home game in the first round of the Class 5A playoffs.
